<TITLE> Man facing murder case hangs himself </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 7 (bdnews24.com)  Police recovered the body of a 24 year-old man on Saturday, who locals said had hung himself to avoid arrest in connection with the abduction and murder of a child in Keraniganj. Police went to Narayan Chandra Mondol's home at Shikaritala on Friday night to arrest him but did not find him there, Keraniganj police chief Asaduzzaman told bdnews24.com. Mandol, with associates, was accused of kidnapping and killing 9 year-old Anamika Ghosh by choking her to death. Neighbours informed the police early Saturday that Narayan had committed suicide by hanging. "We were later able to recover the body," said Asaduzzaman. They also arrested five menidentified as Alauddin, Johnny, Anwar, Kamrul and Manikand recovered Tk 1 lakh taken as ransom from the child's parents. Asaduzzman said Anamika, daughter of Sudharam Ghosh, was abducted on Feb 26. "The kidnappers demanded Tk 8 lakh. Sudhram gave Tk 2.10 lakh to the kidnappers to save the life of his child," said the police chief. Receiving no information about his daughter, Sudharam went to the police. "We notified all the police stations of the matter," said Asaduzzaman. Shibalaya police found a child's body on March 1 and informed Keranaiganj police, who with the father identified it as Anamika. bdnew
